15
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:09,780
♫Hold my hand, Baby♫

16
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:12,980
[Desires in the Wind]

17
00:01:13,350 --> 00:01:16,110
[Previously]
I don’t need you in my life anymore.

18
00:01:16,110 --> 00:01:17,950
I hope you'll understand.

19
00:01:19,730 --> 00:01:23,580
Do you believe me now that you can’t follow the protocol for this matter?

20
00:01:24,100 --> 00:01:25,460
I’m going to keep my promise.

21
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:27,530
I’ll respect your decision.

22
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,130
Where are we going?

23
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:31,000
My older sister’s house in Hua Hin.

24
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:32,750
Don’t you have any cash on you?

25
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:34,000
Why can’t we just take the bus?

26
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:35,660
You’ve just arrived and must be exhausted.

27
00:01:35,729 --> 00:01:36,660
Please go get some rest.

28
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:37,860
Thank you.

29
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:43,009
Considering Miss Blew’s situation right now, all I could do is hide her somewhere safe.

30
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:45,600
Your island. Your private island, Fai.

31
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,710
My father said the suspects have been arrested.

32
00:01:47,710 --> 00:01:52,050
Now, we wait for Fah then we’ll go to Fai's private island.

33
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:59,780
Yes, I plan to feature it in the headlines.

34
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,910
But I need to confirm it with my informant first.

35
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,950
I’ll get it done as soon as possible.

36
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:05,300
Fah.

37
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,130
Yes?

38
00:02:08,130 --> 00:02:11,530
That news you’ve asked me to write–about a clash between the cops and suspects in Chiang Rai.

39
00:02:11,980 --> 00:02:14,330
It’s done. Do you want me to post it now?

40
00:02:15,060 --> 00:02:16,579
Let me see it first.

41
00:02:19,860 --> 00:02:21,950
Mhm, it’s good. Go ahead and post it.

42
00:02:22,350 --> 00:02:27,480
Make sure to hype up the story, so that people would be keen to know who these suspects are.

43
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:28,700
Sure.

44
00:02:41,860 --> 00:02:45,510
We’re lucky they tried to cover up the news and didn’t mention anything about the princess’s security team.

45
00:02:46,060 --> 00:02:49,710
But the news is hitting every headline, what if those reporters try to dig up more…

46
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:51,780
and find out we’ve tried to kill the princess?

47
00:02:52,530 --> 00:02:53,329
Don’t worry.

48
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:57,050
I already told our men to lay low and don’t make any move during this time.

49
00:02:57,050 --> 00:02:59,550
Not until we can locate the princess.

50
00:03:00,910 --> 00:03:05,880
Good. And make sure those arrested will keep their mouths shut forever.

51
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:07,910
That’s a punishment for failing their job.

52
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:33,730
It’s late, what is weighing on your mind still?

53
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:39,480
I’m merely thinking about Sister.

54
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:44,780
You and your sister have never been apart this long.

55
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:47,150
You must miss her so dearly.

56
00:03:49,460 --> 00:03:50,660
That’s not all, Father.

57
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:56,810
Not only that I miss her, but I’m also worried.

58
00:03:57,730 --> 00:03:59,910
What is it that you’re worried about?

59
00:04:04,930 --> 00:04:10,010
I had a chance to speak with her on the phone, but something about her seemed off.

60
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,280
As if she were someone I barely knew.

61
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:17,380
She couldn’t recall anything we used to talk about

62
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:20,709
Did you get me a souvenir from Thailand, Sister?

63
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,960
What is it that you want?

64
00:04:27,130 --> 00:04:29,710
An inhaler. Don’t you remember?

65
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:37,380
Oh, sorry, I forgot.

66
00:04:37,380 --> 00:04:39,950
Can I get you something from Japan inste

67
00:04:41,159 --> 00:04:42,750
What do you want?

68
00:04:47,530 --> 00:04:49,900
I already told you what I want from Japan.

69
00:04:50,659 --> 00:04:52,080
Don’t you remember, Sister?

70
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:02,880
I have to go now, Karel. I’ll talk to you later.

71
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:15,510
All those things we used to talk about, she couldn’t remember anything.

72
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:23,210
Your sister is probably too exhausted from her hectic schedule.

73
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:26,050
Please don’t overthink it.

74
00:05:26,930 --> 00:05:28,750
I also hope that would be the case, Father.

75
00:05:30,930 --> 00:05:37,409
According to Madelin’s rules, you will be able to help lighten your sister’s burden of responsibility in three years.

76
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:43,080
And once she ascends the throne, you can stay by her side as her supreme secretary.

77
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:53,750
When that day comes, I do hope you will be another great support to help bring further prosperity to our country.

78
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:58,310
I shall never disappoint her.

79
00:06:00,330 --> 00:06:01,130
F**k!

80
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,850
Find out where that bloody princess is!

81
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:07,750
Yes, sir.

82
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:09,010
Yes, sir.

83
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:28,130
Miss Blew?

84
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:31,960
Miss Blew.

85
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,330
Please pardon me.

86
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,000
Miss Blew.

87
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:56,860
Miss Blew?

88
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:01,730
Miss Blew?

89
00:07:07,660 --> 00:07:08,460
Miss Blew!

90
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,160
Miss Blew!

91
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,360
Miss Blew!

92
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:22,600
Miss Blew!

93
00:07:23,660 --> 00:07:24,460
Miss Blew!

94
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:26,210
Miss Vayo!

95
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:27,780
I’m over here!

96
00:07:32,530 --> 00:07:34,480
Why did you leave the house without telling me first?

97
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:36,510
What if anything bad happens?

98
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,210
I just needed a walk.

99
00:07:39,810 --> 00:07:42,250
Please don’t worry about me that much.

100
00:07:42,250 --> 00:07:43,200
I’m fine.

101
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,750
Just having you out of my sight already makes me worried.

102
00:07:56,100 --> 00:08:01,410
I mean, I’m your bodyguard so I must keep watch over you all the time.

103
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,580
I appreciate that.

104
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:10,710
But please don't let your worry stress yourself out. I’m really fine.

105
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:14,560
But the weather here is quite hot indeed.

106
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:17,510
Could you do me a favour, Miss Vayo?

107
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:56,400
I saw a leaf in there, so I just removed it.

108
00:08:58,860 --> 00:09:00,110
Thank you.

109
00:10:20,310 --> 00:10:21,550
I’m sorry.

110
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,310
Did you just kiss someone?

111
00:10:45,850 --> 00:10:48,950
Aww, looking so flustered.

112
00:10:50,530 --> 00:10:51,500
When did you get here?

113
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:56,350
Have you fallen for the princess now?

114
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:57,360
What?

115
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:02,410
Usually, it’s you flirting and making girls falling for you.

116
00:11:02,530 --> 00:11:04,810
This is the first time I’ve seen you being the victim instead.

117
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:06,650
Karma is catching up to you.

118
00:11:06,650 --> 00:11:07,700
Stop being delusional.

119
00:11:07,930 --> 00:11:10,650
Hey, not so fast.

120
00:11:12,010 --> 00:11:15,710
You can fool anyone all you like but you can’t fool me.

121
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:19,310
I see the way you look at Miss Blew.

122
00:11:19,660 --> 00:11:22,100
I can sense there’s definitely something there.

123
00:11:23,060 --> 00:11:25,980
Sense what? Nonsense!

124
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:42,310
Come eat together, Miss Vayo.

125
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:46,180
I’m not hungry

126
00:11:47,930 --> 00:11:50,350
But it’s time to eat.

127
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:52,610
I’m not hungry.

128
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,650
Then, I’m not eating either.

129
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:59,780
Wait. I’ll eat. Let’s eat.

130
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,510
Why are you standing so far away?

131
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:15,280
Come closer.

132
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,750
Is that what you call close?

133
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:34,910
Yes. This is close enough.

134
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:43,700
What’s wrong?

135
00:12:45,660 --> 00:12:47,130
I think I got dust in my eye.

136
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:50,680
Please let me see.

137
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:57,010
Don’t rub it.

138
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:09,080
Can you blow it?

139
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:11,160
What?

140
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:17,350
When I was little and got dust in my eye, Father would always blow it for me.

141
00:13:56,860 --> 00:13:58,350
Thank you.

142
00:13:59,330 --> 00:14:00,130
You’re welcome.

143
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,180
I have a question.

144
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:36,530
Are you still mad at me?

145
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:39,380
What do you mean?

146
00:14:40,900 --> 00:14:42,900
That time when I said I didn’t need you anymore.

147
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,350
It made you upset.

148
00:14:47,660 --> 00:14:48,980
It’s not about that.

149
00:14:49,660 --> 00:14:51,480
Who would dare to get mad at you?

150
00:14:52,330 --> 00:14:54,750
And that was also many days ago.

151
00:14:58,300 --> 00:14:59,100
I thought so too.

152
00:15:09,860 --> 00:15:13,980
So, if you’re not mad, why are you stepping away?

153
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,730
It’s for another reason.

154
00:15:21,060 --> 00:15:23,530
What is it? Can you tell me?

155
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,260
Rightness.

156
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:35,580
I don’t understand.

157
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:44,580
You are a princess while I’m just a commoner.

158
00:15:45,150 --> 00:15:50,480
Between us, there will always be a line that I can never cross.

159
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:57,780
I still don’t understand.

160
00:16:25,260 --> 00:16:28,550
Is this the line of rightness?

161
00:16:30,460 --> 00:16:35,710
Yes, and I can never cross it.

162
00:16:38,130 --> 00:16:42,530
From now on, I’m afraid you and I…

163
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,810
I’m afraid we…

164
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:53,330
We…

165
00:16:53,330 --> 00:16:55,160
I will cross that line to be with you.

166
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:22,260
Yes?

167
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:32,080
Now, you and I are standing on the same side

168
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:40,810
Please act normal and be yourself.

169
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:48,110
I hate it when you treat me like a stranger.

170
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:15,400
I will cross that line to be with you.

171
00:18:35,330 --> 00:18:38,980
Does the princess’s charm still leave you on cloud nine, Sis?

172
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:40,860
Are you stalking me or what?

173
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:46,180
Of course not. I just happen to smell someone in love.

174
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:50,160
I think it probably comes from here.

175
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:51,560
Stop it.

176
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:55,280
Why are you still here?

177
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:57,210
I thought you said you’d go get things ready for the island trip.

178
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:58,610
I’m about to leave.

179
00:18:58,610 --> 00:19:00,610
Just want to say bye to you and the princess first.

180
00:19:00,610 --> 00:19:02,650
See you at the pier then.

181
00:19:02,700 --> 00:19:03,560
Be safe.

182
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:12,480
Hold on, not so fast.

183
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:15,100
What?

184
00:19:16,060 --> 00:19:17,800
I’m your sibling, Sis.

185
00:19:18,260 --> 00:19:20,310
I can see right through you.

186
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:24,710
If she’s the one, then just go for it. What are you waiting for?

187
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:29,400
Aren’t you going to stop me like Din and Nam?

188
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:36,050
No. Why do we have to create conditions in life that would make ourselves unhappy?

189
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:39,250
Isn't it better to make the most of every day and be happy with it?

190
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:44,810
Besides, nobody knows if we’ll even live to see tomorrow.

191
00:19:45,180 --> 00:19:50,080
You’re so lucky to finally find someone you’ve been waiting for. So, just go for it.

192
00:19:50,380 --> 00:19:54,610
Go all in. So that you won’t regret it later.

193
00:19:58,730 --> 00:19:59,700
Are you sure?

194
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:05,110
The princess already crossed the line, didn’t she?

195
00:20:05,130 --> 00:20:05,930
Were you snooping?

196
00:20:06,410 --> 00:20:11,850
No! I was just looking for you and didn’t want to interrupt.

197
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:19,180
Let’s just say, no matter what you decide, I’m always here to support you.

198
00:20:21,010 --> 00:20:22,050
Thanks.

199
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:28,150
Just promise me that you and Miss Blew will stay safe.

200
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:30,580
Can you do that?

201
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:35,280
Sure. Thanks a lot for your concern.

202
00:20:37,660 --> 00:20:38,950
Who’s concerned?

203
00:20:39,130 --> 00:20:40,100
You, of course.

204
00:20:42,360 --> 00:20:44,080
Don’t get emotional.

205
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:46,460
I really can’t deal with this version of y

206
00:20:47,330 --> 00:20:49,350
- Come on, Little Sis.
- Geez, go away!

207
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:51,010
- Give it a try.
- No way!

208
00:20:51,010 --> 00:20:52,450
- Give it a try.
- No way! Don’t do it. What’s got into you?

209
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:56,650
- Give it a try.
- No way! Don’t do it. What’s got into you?

210
00:20:56,650 --> 00:20:58,550
Come on, just try it.

211
00:20:59,000 --> 00:20:59,800
Let’s go.

212
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:00,960
Get off me!

213
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:04,410
Thanks a lot. I’m so touched.

214
00:22:02,860 --> 00:22:05,530
Nobody knows if we’ll even live to see tomorrow.

215
00:22:06,060 --> 00:22:08,330
You’re lucky you’ve found that person you’ve been waiting for.

216
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:12,650
So, just go for it. Give it your all.

217
00:22:36,260 --> 00:22:38,180
Today, I’ll teach you how to use a gun.

218
00:22:38,180 --> 00:22:41,710
So that you can use it to protect yourself in case of emergency.

219
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:46,410
I’ll do my best so that I can protect you too.

220
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:52,380
You don’t have to protect me. It is my job to protect you, Miss Blew.

221
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:55,460
You’ve sacrificed yourself for me.

222
00:22:55,900 --> 00:22:59,080
I want to do something for you too. Please let me do it.

223
00:23:01,530 --> 00:23:02,730
Let’s begin, shall we?

224
00:23:07,960 --> 00:23:10,400
Try holding the gun in a position that you feel most comfortable.

225
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:22,600
Keep your finger off the trigger.

226
00:23:28,330 --> 00:23:30,950
Now try to aim at the target.

227
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:35,750
You’ve never used a gun before.

228
00:23:36,130 --> 00:23:38,250
Let’s not do it with one hand. It’s dangerous.

229
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:46,450
Use both hands to make it steady.

230
00:23:47,780 --> 00:23:54,650
So that when you fire, it would be more accurate.

231
00:23:57,930 --> 00:23:58,860
Okay, got it.

232
00:24:00,760 --> 00:24:01,560
Good.

233
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:07,450
Now, let’s try shooting it.

234
00:24:09,460 --> 00:24:12,180
So that you’ll learn the force when the gun fires and kicks back.

235
00:24:16,460 --> 00:24:18,350
Don’t be scared. I’m right here.

236
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:30,150
For the first shot, I’ll help support the gun for you just to be safe.

237
00:24:35,730 --> 00:24:36,560
Please allow me.

238
00:24:44,060 --> 00:24:45,550
Relax, don’t be afraid.

239
00:24:47,280 --> 00:24:49,110
I’ll count to three.

240
00:24:50,350 --> 00:24:53,280
After that, you can pull the trigger.

241
00:24:56,450 --> 00:25:00,680
One, two, three.

242
00:25:26,260 --> 00:25:27,650
Let’s call it a day.

243
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:29,160
I’m tired now.

244
00:25:56,760 --> 00:26:01,550
Just shooting for the first time, why is my heart beating so fast?

245
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:31,010
Sorry, are you the Princess of Madelin?

246
00:26:31,010 --> 00:26:33,310
No, I’m not the princess.

247
00:26:33,860 --> 00:26:36,010
Can we take a picture with you, please?

248
00:26:36,530 --> 00:26:37,750
No taking pictures. Stop!

249
00:26:37,750 --> 00:26:39,050
Of course, you are!

250
00:26:39,050 --> 00:26:40,150
Please, stop!

251
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:43,610
Stop! I said stop!

252
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:44,900
Wait!

253
00:26:44,900 --> 00:26:46,910
- Please wait.
- Please stop! Stop!

254
00:26:49,410 --> 00:26:50,310
Please.

255
00:26:50,310 --> 00:26:53,810
Put that away now! It’s illegal. I could sue you.

256
00:26:54,450 --> 00:26:56,550
Oh, okay. Sorry.

257
00:26:56,660 --> 00:26:57,800
Please delete all the photos.

258
00:26:58,730 --> 00:27:02,980
Oh Okay.

259
00:27:07,950 --> 00:27:10,280
- I deleted them already.
- Sorry about it.

260
00:27:10,730 --> 00:27:13,450
- Sorry.
- Have a nice day.

261
00:27:16,400 --> 00:27:17,200
Let's go.

262
00:27:23,760 --> 00:27:24,560
I’m sorry.

263
00:27:26,300 --> 00:27:27,330
Don’t worry about it.

264
00:27:28,160 --> 00:27:29,810
Will the photos get out?

265
00:27:30,460 --> 00:27:31,260
I don’t think so.

266
00:27:31,660 --> 00:27:32,600
Hey, Lom.

267
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:34,610
Fah! You’re early.

268
00:27:34,610 --> 00:27:38,450
This is Fah, the reporter cousin I told you about.

269
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:39,960
Hello.

270
00:27:40,300 --> 00:27:41,100
Hello.

271
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:45,850
My informant in Madelin said King Arthur is still safe.

272
00:27:46,180 --> 00:27:47,610
There’s no sign of rebellion there.

273
00:27:47,610 --> 00:27:50,080
And no one knows about the fake princess either.

274
00:27:51,660 --> 00:27:57,250
If Sir Antione still hasn’t made any move by now, I’m afraid this is only Grace and Henri’s doing.

275
00:27:58,530 --> 00:28:01,310
Then, should we find a way to inform King Arthur?

276
00:28:03,300 --> 00:28:06,810
I’ve asked you to come because I have a way to do that.

277
00:28:07,110 --> 00:28:09,450
But I might need your help.

278
00:28:09,800 --> 00:28:10,600
How?

279
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:15,150
I’d like you to deliver my letter to Prince Karel.

280
00:28:16,700 --> 00:28:19,510
But how can she do that without drawing anyone’s attention?

281
00:28:23,780 --> 00:28:28,880
Usually, Karel will pay his friend in France a private visit every month.

282
00:28:29,510 --> 00:28:32,310
We can secretly contact him during that time.

283
00:28:32,750 --> 00:28:34,880
Please give my letter to Karel there.

284
00:28:35,310 --> 00:28:38,710
Once Karel reads it, he will surely find a way to send help.

285
00:28:39,050 --> 00:28:40,750
I’ll prepare everything for you.

286
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:44,310
Okay, I’ll go to France…

287
00:28:44,310 --> 00:28:47,480
and hand your letter to the Prince myself.

288
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:50,460
Thank you.

289
00:28:51,660 --> 00:28:52,460
It’s my pleasure.

290
00:29:08,460 --> 00:29:10,200
Is that Madelin language?

291
00:29:12,060 --> 00:29:14,980
Wouldn’t it be dangerous if those criminals get the letter?

292
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:18,410
This is the royal family’s secret language.

293
00:29:18,410 --> 00:29:22,410
Only those in the family would understand.

294
00:29:22,410 --> 00:29:26,650
Which means only Father and Karel can understand it.

295
00:29:29,360 --> 00:29:31,400
Do you want to learn it, Miss Vayo?

296
00:29:31,930 --> 00:29:33,110
I can teach you.

297
00:29:34,530 --> 00:29:37,450
Maybe not. I’m not part of the royal family.

298
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:42,650
But you saved my life. You’re someone the royal family remains grateful for.

299
00:29:44,460 --> 00:29:45,260
Come and sit here.

300
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,000
Please pardon me.

301
00:29:54,560 --> 00:29:58,180
You can just teach me some words,

302
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:01,610
so that we can use them to contact each other in case of emergency.

303
00:30:03,660 --> 00:30:04,930
What should I teach you then?

304
00:30:13,410 --> 00:30:16,580
‘I’ is like this.

305
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:25,510
This is ‘You’.

306
00:30:32,100 --> 00:30:36,210
What about ‘Princess is safe’?

307
00:30:38,610 --> 00:30:46,250
‘Princess is safe’ is like this.

308
00:30:49,860 --> 00:30:52,910
‘Princess is safe’ is like this.

309
00:30:59,100 --> 00:31:00,350
Like this.

310
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:03,810
[Princess, run away.]

311
00:31:04,930 --> 00:31:11,550
If I write you this word, you must run.

312
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:15,110
Okay.

313
00:31:28,930 --> 00:31:32,610
What does this word mean?

314
00:31:33,500 --> 00:31:34,510
It means ‘Love’

315
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:46,680
You’re so lucky to have found someone you’ve been waiting for. So, go for it.

316
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:48,180
Just go all in.

317
00:32:03,800 --> 00:32:08,910
What does this mean then?

318
00:32:11,310 --> 00:32:15,080
[Love Princess]

319
00:32:42,530 --> 00:32:43,750
Lom.

320
00:32:50,460 --> 00:32:51,930
I’m here to take the letter.

321
00:32:53,480 --> 00:32:55,180
I’ve just finished writing it.

322
00:33:12,460 --> 00:33:15,380
This is Sebastian’s address, the Prince’s friend.

323
00:33:15,380 --> 00:33:19,780
If Sebastian doesn’t believe you, please show him the clip I recorded for you.

324
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:21,000
Yes.

325
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:23,380
I’m counting on you.

326
00:33:24,100 --> 00:33:27,310
Please don’t worry. I’ll get everything done as fast as I can.

327
00:33:28,500 --> 00:33:29,380
Thanks a lot.

328
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:33,450
It’s nothing, Sis. No need to thank me.

329
00:33:34,130 --> 00:33:37,550
Are you going to Fai’s island tomorrow? Have a safe trip then.

330
00:33:38,300 --> 00:33:39,900
Are you leaving today?

331
00:33:41,050 --> 00:33:42,410
Yes, I think so.

332
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:44,310
But you’ve just arrived.

333
00:33:46,100 --> 00:33:47,780
Didn’t you want me to help?

334
00:33:51,660 --> 00:33:53,580
Have a safe journey, Miss Fah.

335
00:33:53,700 --> 00:33:54,650
Thank you.

336
00:34:05,730 --> 00:34:07,950
Are you done packing everything, Miss Blew?

337
00:34:08,460 --> 00:34:10,110
I don’t have much to pack.

338
00:34:10,179 --> 00:34:14,380
Then, should I take you to buy more things before we get on a boat?

339
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:17,810
It’s all right. What you’ve given me is quite enough.

340
00:34:18,730 --> 00:34:22,350
I’m afraid not. We’ll be going somewhere quite deserted.

341
00:34:23,080 --> 00:34:24,750
No shops or restaurants there.

342
00:34:24,750 --> 00:34:28,050
If you don’t buy it beforehand, you might have a hard time there.

343
00:34:29,699 --> 00:34:31,650
Aren’t we going to Miss Fai’s house?

344
00:34:33,100 --> 00:34:38,010
Not her house but her private island that Uncle Ak, Fai’s father, bought for her.

345
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:43,250
What business is he doing? Why did he need to buy an island?

346
00:34:44,860 --> 00:34:49,310
Well, there’s mining, palm plantation, and also rubber plantation.

347
00:34:49,310 --> 00:34:52,480
Pretty much everything a businessman can do in Surat.

348
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:58,650
But if I go there, will it cause people on that island any trouble?

349
00:35:00,160 --> 00:35:01,880
Please don’t worry.

350
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:07,150
It’s a private island–only a few fisherman families live there.

351
00:35:07,150 --> 00:35:08,510
You can only get there by boat.

352
00:35:08,510 --> 00:35:11,680
If those goons try to come to the island, we’ll know right away.

353
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:15,980
I really can’t picture what it’d be like.

354
00:35:31,560 --> 00:35:33,050
Are you sure they’re here?

355
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:37,610
Yes, from those photos I saw on social media, it’s definitely here.

356
00:35:37,980 --> 00:35:40,810
They’re staying further back in a VIP zone.

357
00:35:41,530 --> 00:35:44,350
Be discreet and don’t draw any attention this time.

358
00:35:45,680 --> 00:35:46,510
Yes, sir.

359
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:11,400
Hold on.

360
00:36:15,100 --> 00:36:17,410
Miss Nam told me to bring you some snacks, Miss.

361
00:36:17,500 --> 00:36:19,780
I see. Thank you.

362
00:36:23,360 --> 00:36:26,930
Excuse me, what is my older sister, Fai, doing?

363
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:30,650
She’s already in bed, Miss.

364
00:36:31,930 --> 00:36:32,730
Thank you.

365
00:36:44,130 --> 00:36:46,350
Miss Blew, wake up. Miss Blew.

366
00:36:48,760 --> 00:36:49,880
What happened?

367
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:51,950
They’ve found us.

368
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:00,730
The pills should have their effect by now.

369
00:37:00,780 --> 00:37:01,750
Let’s go.

370
00:37:03,500 --> 00:37:05,780
You go downstairs. And you, upstairs.

371
00:37:11,330 --> 00:37:12,130
Wait.

372
00:37:13,760 --> 00:37:17,110
They know we’re here, but probably haven’t gone that far.

373
00:37:17,960 --> 00:37:18,930
Search the whole place.

374
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:39,410
That’s it. Come and get more tomorrow.

375
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:40,460
Sure.

376
00:38:55,660 --> 00:38:56,410
Thank you.

377
00:38:56,410 --> 00:38:58,610
Yeah. Is that all? Make sure to recheck it.

378
00:40:05,200 --> 00:40:06,980
It’s all right. You’re safe now.

379
00:40:31,730 --> 00:40:35,150
Hey! The towels are already here.

380
00:40:35,150 --> 00:40:36,880
Why don’t you unload them?

381
00:40:41,560 --> 00:40:42,400
Lom!

382
00:40:46,560 --> 00:40:48,950
Lom! It’s really you!

383
00:40:51,680 --> 00:40:53,310
I miss you so much!

384
00:40:53,710 --> 00:40:56,710
It’s really you in the flesh! I miss you so much!

385
00:40:56,930 --> 00:40:58,710
Hi, Buahima.

386
00:40:58,860 --> 00:41:02,680
Oh my gosh, you remember me?

387
00:41:02,980 --> 00:41:10,080
Do you know that after you left,

388
00:41:10,080 --> 00:41:13,750
I couldn’t eat or sleep for months?

389
00:41:13,750 --> 00:41:15,410
I’m sorry.

390
00:41:15,410 --> 00:41:19,250
I forgive you but…

391
00:41:25,060 --> 00:41:25,860
Really?

392
00:41:26,160 --> 00:41:26,960
Yes.

393
00:41:32,360 --> 00:41:33,160
You’re naughty!

394
00:41:35,300 --> 00:41:39,250
Oh, by the way, why are you here?

395
00:41:39,730 --> 00:41:40,950
I’m here to catch the criminals.

396
00:41:41,560 --> 00:41:43,060
I’m on a secret mission.

397
00:41:43,460 --> 00:41:46,750
It’d be safer for you if you don’t know about it.

398
00:41:46,760 --> 00:41:50,510
Hold on, are you hurt anywhere?

399
00:41:50,810 --> 00:41:51,910
Tell me if you’re hurt anywhere.

400
00:41:51,910 --> 00:41:54,110
Oh, are you hurt anywhere?

401
00:41:54,110 --> 00:41:57,280
My precious Lom. My sweet baby, you’re safe now.

402
00:41:57,960 --> 00:41:59,650
I’m so worried about you.

403
00:41:59,730 --> 00:42:00,530
Yes.

404
00:42:05,360 --> 00:42:10,980
So, who’s this girl that looks less pretty than me?

405
00:42:11,560 --> 00:42:12,780
She’s my colleague.

406
00:42:13,160 --> 00:42:15,510
We’re working on a mission together.

407
00:42:16,260 --> 00:42:17,610
Your colleague?

408
00:42:18,900 --> 00:42:22,780
Buahima, can you possibly find someone to drop me off in Surat Thani?

409
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:30,260
If that’s what you want, I can always make it happen.

410
00:42:33,200 --> 00:42:34,810
It’s a top secret though.

411
00:42:36,460 --> 00:42:37,330
Got it, top secret.

412
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:42,480
Aww, you’re as lovely as ever.

413
00:42:42,730 --> 00:42:46,280
Please wait here. I’ll get it done for you in a jiff.

414
00:42:46,330 --> 00:42:47,130
Thank you.

415
00:42:53,100 --> 00:42:56,880
Kiddo! I need to use one of the cars.

416
00:42:56,880 --> 00:42:58,350
Give me one.

417
00:43:05,530 --> 00:43:08,310
You’re so popular, Miss Vayo.

418
00:43:08,310 --> 00:43:10,250
It seems you have an admirer in every province.

419
00:43:10,760 --> 00:43:11,800
Oh, not that much.

420
00:43:12,500 --> 00:43:13,950
So, almost then?

421
00:43:47,700 --> 00:43:48,500
Let’s go.

422
00:43:55,130 --> 00:43:55,930
Fai!

423
00:43:58,530 --> 00:43:59,450
Lom!

424
00:44:00,150 --> 00:44:01,450
Go get the boat ready.

425
00:44:01,530 --> 00:44:02,610
Yes, Young Boss.

426
00:44:09,260 --> 00:44:11,080
What’s the situation at the resort?

427
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:14,510
Nam said she found traces of intruders there.

428
00:44:14,700 --> 00:44:16,000
There were probably 3-4 of them.

429
00:44:16,260 --> 00:44:19,600
But Nam already told the police to collect whatever evidence there is.

430
00:44:20,360 --> 00:44:22,350
They’ve found us much faster than I thought.

431
00:44:24,530 --> 00:44:25,950
The boat is ready, Young Boss.

432
00:44:28,730 --> 00:44:30,610
Do we have to get on this boat?

433
00:44:31,160 --> 00:44:33,450
Yes, are you okay with it, Miss Blew?

434
00:44:35,560 --> 00:44:40,350
I’m fine. I’m just surprised. I’ve never travelled on a boat like this before.

435
00:44:42,060 --> 00:44:43,650
Lom, this is Yod.

436
00:44:44,930 --> 00:44:45,500
Hello.

437
00:44:45,500 --> 00:44:47,310
Yod will take you to the island.

438
00:44:47,310 --> 00:44:49,110
Once there, Uncle Boonsong will come to pick you up.

439
00:44:49,960 --> 00:44:52,500
One more thing, there’s no phone signal on the island.

440
00:44:52,600 --> 00:44:56,580
If there’s any update, I’ll let you know through Uncle Boonsong.

441
00:44:56,580 --> 00:44:58,750
Or tell him if you need anything.

442
00:44:58,800 --> 00:44:59,950
He’s coming ashore every weekend.

443
00:45:00,660 --> 00:45:01,460
Okay.

444
00:45:02,100 --> 00:45:03,280
Take care of them for me, Yod.

445
00:45:03,650 --> 00:45:06,710
And don’t you ever tell my dad about this.

446
00:45:06,900 --> 00:45:07,810
Sure, Young Boss.

447
00:45:08,110 --> 00:45:10,350
I’ll never let the Master know about this.

448
00:45:11,330 --> 00:45:12,650
Come, let’s get you on a boat.

449
00:45:14,060 --> 00:45:15,580
Take care, Lom.

450
00:45:15,860 --> 00:45:16,660
See you later.

451
00:45:17,260 --> 00:45:17,750
Let’s go.

452
00:45:17,750 --> 00:45:18,610
This way, Miss.

453
00:45:47,330 --> 00:45:48,910
Are you okay, Miss Blew?

454
00:45:53,760 --> 00:45:54,850
I’m good.

455
00:45:55,800 --> 00:45:58,410
But you don’t look so well though.

456
00:46:09,700 --> 00:46:12,110
Smell this. It might help.

457
00:46:43,530 --> 00:46:45,750
Miss Blew! Miss Blew!

458
00:46:52,460 --> 00:46:53,260
Are you all right?

459
00:46:58,800 --> 00:47:00,080
Miss Blew, are you okay?

460
00:47:00,530 --> 00:47:01,510
Are you all right?

461
00:47:05,860 --> 00:47:08,110
Please hang in there. We’re almost at the safehouse.

462
00:47:24,400 --> 00:47:25,980
Oh, you’re here?

463
00:47:27,600 --> 00:47:28,580
Paka!

464
00:47:28,730 --> 00:47:29,530
Yes?

465
00:47:29,660 --> 00:47:30,450
Hi, Uncle.

466
00:47:30,450 --> 00:47:31,580
Hello there.

467
00:47:32,160 --> 00:47:33,530
Come in.

468
00:47:33,900 --> 00:47:34,700
Please come in.

469
00:47:36,000 --> 00:47:36,760
Hello.

470
00:47:36,760 --> 00:47:39,660
Hello, girls. Come on in. Come and sit down.

471
00:47:39,760 --> 00:47:40,200
Hello.

472
00:47:40,200 --> 00:47:43,210
This is Uncle Boonsong, a village chief on this island.

473
00:47:44,200 --> 00:47:47,150
And this is Phaka, my wife.

474
00:47:47,560 --> 00:47:48,330
Hello.

475
00:47:48,330 --> 00:47:49,130
Hello.

476
00:47:49,900 --> 00:47:51,880
And my daughter–hey, kiddo!

477
00:47:51,960 --> 00:47:52,760
Yes, Dad?

478
00:47:52,900 --> 00:47:53,700
Come here, quick!

479
00:47:53,900 --> 00:47:56,810
Geez, Dad. I’m working.

480
00:47:56,810 --> 00:47:57,880
This kid and her endless whining.

481
00:48:12,600 --> 00:48:13,400
My daughter.

482
00:48:21,860 --> 00:48:25,180
Hi, I’m Bua.

483
00:48:27,300 --> 00:48:28,580
Another Bua?

484
00:48:30,080 --> 00:48:34,050
May I know your names?

485
00:48:35,360 --> 00:48:36,010
I’m–

486
00:48:36,010 --> 00:48:37,150
Phatpha.

487
00:48:38,130 --> 00:48:40,710
Her name is Phatpha. But you can call her Phat.

488
00:48:44,060 --> 00:48:46,850
What about you, Pretty girl

489
00:48:46,850 --> 00:48:47,450
I’m–

490
00:48:47,460 --> 00:48:48,360
Wind.

491
00:48:51,130 --> 00:48:56,010
Wind–that’s a beautiful name, don’t you think so, Mum?

492
00:48:59,860 --> 00:49:03,710
Young Boss already told me everything, so please don’t worry.

493
00:49:04,100 --> 00:49:05,460
We’ll take really good care of you.

494
00:49:06,960 --> 00:49:09,650
If you need anything, you can always tell us.

495
00:49:09,930 --> 00:49:12,550
Or if you need an errand, Bua can also do it for you.

496
00:49:13,130 --> 00:49:17,110
That’s right. I’m at your beck and call for 24-7.

497
00:49:18,330 --> 00:49:19,510
Any time at all.

498
00:49:21,560 --> 00:49:23,380
It’s very nice to meet all of you.

499
00:49:23,730 --> 00:49:24,530
Yes.

500
00:49:25,330 --> 00:49:30,180
We’ve arranged a place for you to stay but it’s quite far–at the end of the beach.

501
00:49:30,730 --> 00:49:32,410
But it’s very private.

502
00:49:32,410 --> 00:49:33,910
Quiet and not so many people there.

503
00:49:34,500 --> 00:49:37,980
Too bad there's no phone signal there.

504
00:49:38,650 --> 00:49:42,810
If you want to contact someone onshore, just come to my house.

505
00:49:42,810 --> 00:49:44,350
You’ll get a full signal there.

506
00:49:45,300 --> 00:49:48,710
Thank you so much for taking the trouble to arrange everything for us.

507
00:49:49,950 --> 00:49:51,810
Oh, it’s my pleasure.

508
00:49:51,810 --> 00:49:55,180
All of us here are so grateful to Young Boss and the Master.

509
00:49:55,180 --> 00:49:56,650
We’re more than happy to help.

510
00:49:56,660 --> 00:49:57,460
Yes.

511
00:49:57,800 --> 00:49:59,410
Hey, Darling.

512
00:49:59,410 --> 00:49:59,910
What?

513
00:50:00,460 --> 00:50:05,110
Take Miss Wind and Miss Phatpha to their house.

514
00:50:05,110 --> 00:50:09,650
It’s okay, Mum. Just stay here and rest.

515
00:50:09,810 --> 00:50:11,880
Let me take care of it.

516
00:50:12,710 --> 00:50:14,350
Okay. Bua will take you there then.

517
00:50:15,130 --> 00:50:20,410
Please follow me. Be careful too. Please watch your step.

518
00:50:21,100 --> 00:50:22,400
Why is she so hardworking?

519
00:50:22,860 --> 00:50:23,660
I don't know either.

520
00:50:26,330 --> 00:50:28,350
She hardly tells us to be careful.

521
00:50:29,200 --> 00:50:30,860
The weather is really nice today.

522
00:50:31,730 --> 00:50:33,880
Maybe because you’re here, Wind.

523
00:50:35,760 --> 00:50:36,950
We’re almost there.

524
00:50:38,100 --> 00:50:39,160
Please watch your step.

525
00:50:42,700 --> 00:50:45,280
There you go, this is your house.

526
00:50:46,700 --> 00:50:49,650
Miss Fai told us to have everything arranged for you.

527
00:50:51,260 --> 00:50:52,060
Thank you.

528
00:50:54,100 --> 00:50:58,710
If you need anything, just let me know. I’m happy to help.

529
00:51:02,600 --> 00:51:06,010
Thank you so much, Miss Bua. We’ll take it from here.

530
00:51:06,010 --> 00:51:07,650
We’d rather not bother you any further.

531
00:51:09,330 --> 00:51:12,050
Oh, it’s not a bother at all. I want to help.

532
00:51:13,880 --> 00:51:20,610
Well then, I should get going. Remember, I’m at your beck and call for 24-7.

533
00:51:21,930 --> 00:51:22,730
Please go ahead.

534
00:51:23,560 --> 00:51:24,460
I’m off then.

535
00:51:27,660 --> 00:51:30,400
Call me if you need anything.

536
00:51:31,330 --> 00:51:33,250
I can come anytime.

537
00:51:39,960 --> 00:51:41,960
You certainly are very charming, Miss Vayo.

538
00:52:33,260 --> 00:52:35,450
So, this is how people on an island live.

539
00:52:35,900 --> 00:52:37,480
Do you think you can make do with it?

540
00:52:38,060 --> 00:52:41,880
Of course, it’s much better than the fruit and vegetable trucks I used to sleep on.

541
00:52:45,100 --> 00:52:47,880
You’re quicker to adjust than I thought.

542
00:52:48,600 --> 00:52:52,680
We might need to stay here for a while so let’s agree on some rules.

543
00:52:54,860 --> 00:52:55,700
What rules?

544
00:52:58,130 --> 00:53:03,110
While we’re here, we must address each other with our new names so that we’ll get used to it.

545
00:53:04,600 --> 00:53:10,550
Sure. So, I’ll call you Wind and you can call me Phatpha–

546
00:53:10,700 --> 00:53:12,310
the name you’ve given me.

547
00:53:13,080 --> 00:53:13,780
Yes.

548
00:53:16,330 --> 00:53:20,510
Then, you have to drop the ‘Miss’ and just call me by my name.

549
00:53:20,850 --> 00:53:25,580
And talk to me normally. Don’t think of me as a princess.

550
00:53:28,160 --> 00:53:32,550
If not as a princess, then what should I think of you?

551
00:53:46,500 --> 00:53:51,450
Well, as a…close friend!

552
00:53:52,800 --> 00:53:56,150
Fine. Close friend.

553
00:53:57,380 --> 00:53:58,250
Sure.

554
00:54:00,900 --> 00:54:03,900
Any other rules?

555
00:54:08,760 --> 00:54:09,960
While we’re here,

556
00:54:10,330 --> 00:54:13,380
we have to blend in with the people here as much as we can.

557
00:54:14,100 --> 00:54:15,200
So that no one will suspect us.

558
00:54:17,250 --> 00:54:21,350
Okay, I’ll try to blend in as best as I can.

559
00:54:23,000 --> 00:54:24,510
Then, let’s start with…

560
00:54:35,200 --> 00:54:37,350
Can you eat Southern food, Phatpha?

561
00:54:40,360 --> 00:54:43,210
I’ve never eaten it. But I’ll give it a try.

562
00:54:45,200 --> 00:54:47,750
Great! This one is Fermented Fish Entrails Soup.

563
00:54:48,160 --> 00:54:49,150
Sour Soup.

564
00:54:50,130 --> 00:54:51,510
Stir-fried Stink Bean with Prawn.

565
00:54:51,930 --> 00:54:53,610
Stir-fried Malindjo Leaves with Egg.

566
00:54:53,860 --> 00:54:56,950
This one is Sun-dried Squid with Spicy and Sour Seafood Sauce.

567
00:54:58,900 --> 00:54:59,910
Wanna try it?

568
00:55:16,960 --> 00:55:18,410
Why is it so spicy?

569
00:55:20,860 --> 00:55:23,850
That one is probably too spicy for you. Let’s try this one.

570
00:55:36,100 --> 00:55:37,710
I like this one the most.

571
00:55:39,560 --> 00:55:41,080
Then, have the whole dish.

572
00:55:44,860 --> 00:55:46,410
This one too. It’s not spicy.

573
00:55:52,200 --> 00:55:53,780
Aren’t you eating, Wind?

574
00:55:54,500 --> 00:55:56,150
I’ll eat the rest.

575
00:56:02,300 --> 00:56:06,860
They actually look delicious. But I don’t like spicy food.

576
00:56:09,060 --> 00:56:15,450
Tomorrow, I’ll tell Aunt Paka to make an egg menu which is not spicy for you.

577
00:56:17,900 --> 00:56:22,150
Sorry to trouble you and everyone. I’ll try harder to adjust to it.

578
00:56:23,500 --> 00:56:25,250
You’ve done a great job so far.

579
00:56:28,530 --> 00:56:32,950
Eat as much as you like so that we can fight the traitors.

580
00:56:36,200 --> 00:56:40,250
You too, so that you’ll have enough strength to protect me.

581
00:56:52,060 --> 00:56:55,110
I'll return the dishes after we finish eating.

582
00:56:55,530 --> 00:56:59,110
If you want to take a shower, please go ahead.

583
00:57:01,860 --> 00:57:02,660
Okay.

584
00:58:10,130 --> 00:58:12,250
Do I really have to shower here?

585
00:58:21,560 --> 00:58:22,530
It’s cold.

586
00:58:33,550 --> 00:58:34,750
Phatpha!

587
00:58:36,510 --> 00:58:37,410
Phatpha!

588
00:58:42,760 --> 00:58:45,680
What’s going on? What’s wrong, Phatpha?

589
00:58:47,260 --> 00:58:48,510
I’m fine.

590
00:58:48,960 --> 00:58:50,350
Why did you scream then?

591
00:58:52,600 --> 00:58:53,850
The water is cold.

592
00:59:00,000 --> 00:59:02,610
Okay, water is cold.

593
00:59:23,960 --> 00:59:27,250
I’m done setting up the mosquito net. Let’s sleep.

594
00:59:45,500 --> 00:59:47,350
I’ve never slept in a place like this.

595
00:59:47,800 --> 00:59:49,510
The vibe is actually quite nice.

596
00:59:57,700 --> 00:59:59,310
Aren’t you going to sleep, Wind?

597
00:59:59,780 --> 01:00:02,010
I’ll sleep downstairs.

598
01:00:09,300 --> 01:00:10,550
Come sleep here together.

599
01:00:13,260 --> 01:00:14,610
Together?

600
01:00:24,560 --> 01:00:30,010
How could I let you sleep downstairs when I’m the one who has put you into all these troubles?

601
01:00:31,660 --> 01:00:32,930
But it’s not appropriate.

602
01:00:34,130 --> 01:00:39,100
But here, I’m Phatpha–not a gracious princess from somewhere.

603
01:00:40,730 --> 01:00:43,180
You’re the one who told me that, remember?

604
01:00:44,100 --> 01:00:44,930
I remember.

605
01:00:47,330 --> 01:00:51,060
While we’re here, I’ll think of you as my close friend.

606
01:00:56,160 --> 01:00:57,910
Just a close friend?

607
01:01:01,930 --> 01:01:02,760
Pardon?

608
01:01:04,160 --> 01:01:04,960
Nothing.

609
01:01:10,560 --> 01:01:11,700
I want to get some rest now.

610
01:01:36,600 --> 01:01:38,410
Why are you still outside?

611
01:01:39,930 --> 01:01:42,650
Can I just sit and nap here?

612
01:01:44,400 --> 01:01:47,110
No, it’s time to sleep.

613
01:02:42,960 --> 01:02:43,760
Sweet dream.

614
01:02:46,100 --> 01:02:47,100
Goodnight.

615
01:04:23,730 --> 01:04:25,550
You seem to like it here.

616
01:04:27,200 --> 01:04:28,530
I love being here.

617
01:04:30,200 --> 01:04:35,310
Being Phatpha makes me experience freedom for the first time in my life.

618
01:04:36,610 --> 01:04:42,280
I can throw away the royal title I was born with, even for a short while.

619
01:04:44,100 --> 01:04:46,380
And live like a commoner.

620
01:04:47,360 --> 01:04:49,010
I want to learn about this.

621
01:04:49,500 --> 01:04:53,910
So that in the future, I can rule with empathy and understanding.

622
01:04:58,100 --> 01:05:02,150
Then, feel free to be yourself while you’re here.

623
01:05:03,100 --> 01:05:07,850
Be Phatpha that nobody knows who she is or where she is from.

624
01:05:10,300 --> 01:05:13,980
I’ll be Phatpha the way I want her to be.

625
01:05:20,130 --> 01:05:23,950
And I’ll be Wind the way I want.

626
01:05:25,900 --> 01:05:29,200
Your kind of Wind, what is she like?

627
01:05:33,960 --> 01:05:37,650
I’ll just…do whatever my heart says.

628
01:05:44,330 --> 01:05:45,130
I will…

629
01:05:52,130 --> 01:05:52,930
I will…

630
01:05:55,560 --> 01:05:56,360
I’ll…

631
01:06:38,560 --> 01:06:40,700
[Next Episode]
Why didn’t you invite Bua to eat with us too?

632
01:06:41,500 --> 01:06:43,580
I prefer to be with someone I like.

633
01:06:44,060 --> 01:06:47,710
Pretty Miss Phatpha, can I ask you something?

634
01:06:47,800 --> 01:06:48,600
What is it?

635
01:06:48,700 --> 01:06:51,650
Does Win have a girlfriend or someone she likes yet?

636
01:06:51,650 --> 01:06:55,810
If so, I’ll back off. But if not, I’m going to pursue her.

637
01:06:56,130 --> 01:06:58,810
You traitors! I’ll have all of you executed!

638
01:06:58,930 --> 01:06:59,730
What are you doing?

639
01:06:59,860 --> 01:07:01,210
Hey! Don’t touch me!

640
01:07:01,360 --> 01:07:05,450
Last night, I just got drunk and fell asleep, and didn’t do anything weird to you, did I?

641
01:07:05,460 --> 01:07:07,080
You passed out the moment your head hit the pillow.

642
01:07:07,160 --> 01:07:08,450
Was I dreaming?

643
01:07:09,060 --> 01:07:10,680
Was it a good dream or a bad dream?

644
01:07:12,130 --> 01:07:13,380
Good dream, I guess.

645
01:07:41,680 --> 01:07:52,110
♫ I wonder which star it is that guided me to meet you ♫

646
01:07:53,680 --> 01:08:04,710
♫Or is it destiny that has brought us together♫

647
01:08:05,250 --> 01:08:11,250
♫You’re like the wind, carrying me to the sky♫

648
01:08:11,250 --> 01:08:16,250
♫No matter how high, I won’t be afraid♫

649
01:08:16,250 --> 01:08:22,010
♫ Only you is enough, I don’t need anything else ♫

650
01:08:22,010 --> 01:08:30,850
♫ust us together is enough, you’re the meaning in my life♫

651
01:08:30,850 --> 01:08:38,010
♫Every day from now, please stay by my side♫

652
01:08:38,350 --> 01:08:40,479
[Desires in the Wind]
♫and we’ll always have each other♫

653
01:08:40,479 --> 01:08:43,779
[North Star Entertainment]
♫and we’ll always have each other♫

